To terminate a C program, you can use the `exit()` function from the `stdlib.h` library. Here's an example of how to use it:

```c
#include <stdio.h>
#include <stdlib.h>

int main() {
    printf("Hello, World!\n");
    exit(0); // Terminates the program with a successful status code
    return 0;
}
```

